xecutable-based runner instead of VSTest. -detects the runner automatically, but being explicit is safer. I need to check what the latest xUnit v3 version actually is—I'll use 1.0.2 as a reasonable starting point, though I should verify this against NuGet to make sure it's available.\n\nLet me just proceed with the migration using xUnit v3 version 1.0.2 and see if the build works. I'll update the project file and global.json, then test to confirm the versions are correct. I should also verify that the required .NET SDK version is available on the system.","outputTokens":1515,"requestId":"0BC0:1612ED:48511F:546F22:69F010F3"},"id":"e2947a85-3e13-4907-8652-68e0457af649","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:44:52.773Z","parentId":"52554327-76c0-41d8-9de8-617d06b776b2"}
